library(tidyverse)
library(sits)
library(sf)
Linking to GEOS 3.9.3, GDAL 3.5.2, PROJ 8.2.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
# Create a directory to store files
if (!file.exists("../../../tempdir/")) {
  dir.create("../../../tempdir/")
}
# Create an irregular data cube from MSPC
s2_cube <- sits_cube(
  source = "AWS",
  collection = "SENTINEL-S2-L2A-COGS",
  tiles = "48PVU",
  bands = c(
    "B02", "B03", "B04",
    "B05", "B06", "B07",
    "B08", "B8A", "B11",
    "B12", "CLOUD"
  ),
  start_date = as.Date("2018-07-01"),
  end_date = as.Date("2018-08-31")
)

  |                                                                                                               
  |                                                                                                         |   0%
  |                                                                                                               
  |=========================================================================================================| 100%
# Regularize the cube to 15 day intervals
reg_cube <- sits_regularize(
  cube       = s2_cube,
  output_dir = "../../../tempdir/",
  res        = 60,
  period     = "P15D",
  multicores = 4
)
Warning: Regularization works better when data store locally. Please, use 'sits_cube_copy()' to copy data locally before regularization

# Calculate NDVI index using bands B08 and B04
reg_cube <- sits_apply(reg_cube,
  NDVI = (B08 - B04) / (B08 + B04),
  output_dir = "../../../tempdir/",
  multicores = 4,
  memsize = 12
)

plot(reg_cube, date = sits_timeline(reg_cube)[4], band = "NDVI", palette = "RdYlGn")
